com21HcxCc.name: com21HcxCc
com21HcxCc.contactinfo: Network Management Postal: Paul Gordon Com21, Inc. 750 Tasman Drive Milpitas, California 95035 USA Tel: +1 408 953 9100 Fax: +1 408 953 9299 E-mail: pgordon@com21.com
com21HcxCc.description: This is the Com21 ComController Common Control Unit MIB module. COM21 Part# 005-0025-00

hcxCcSlotId.name: hcxCcSlotId
hcxCcSlotId.description: contains the Common Controller slot id.

hcxCcHardwareVersion.name: hcxCcHardwareVersion
hcxCcHardwareVersion.description: contains the hardware version of the CC card.

hcxCcBootVersion.name: hcxCcBootVersion
hcxCcBootVersion.description: contains the version of the CC card boot ROM.

hcxSoftwareRevision.name: hcxSoftwareRevision
hcxSoftwareRevision.description: The Common Controller Software Revision is a display string value which contains the software revision of the currently loaded COM21 Common Controller software downloaded from the software server device.

hcxControlPrimServState.name: hcxControlPrimServState
hcxControlPrimServState.description: contains primary service state of the Common Controller. This attribute indicates the overall service state of the Controller. OOS indicates that complete service cannot be provided. IS indicates that the Controller is operating as normal, though a non-service effecting error or test condition may exist.

hcxControlPrimServStateChange.name: hcxControlPrimServStateChange
hcxControlPrimServStateChange.description: generated whenever hcxControlPrimaryServiceState changes value. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxControlSecServState.name: hcxControlSecServState
hcxControlSecServState.description: contains a string defining the secondary service states of the Common Controller. The states supported by the com21HcxControlGroup are: FAN - indicates Fan Failure, HIGH - indicates high temp condition, PWR - indicates power problem.

hcxControlSecServStateChange.name: hcxControlSecServStateChange
hcxControlSecServStateChange.description: generated whenever hcxControlSecondaryServiceState changes value. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxCcDiagTestAction.name: hcxCcDiagTestAction
hcxCcDiagTestAction.description: This attribute is used to invoke the internal Common Controller diagnostic test. In order to activate this test, the card must be placed in the test state.

hcxCcDiagTestComplete.name: hcxCcDiagTestComplete
hcxCcDiagTestComplete.description: This notification is generated whenever the CC card internal diagnostic tests are completed. Event only, no clear. Only severity allowed is WARNING.

hcxCcDiagTestResult.name: hcxCcDiagTestResult
hcxCcDiagTestResult.description: This attribute contains the result of the last CC card diagnostic test.

hcxCcTestStatusLed.name: hcxCcTestStatusLed
hcxCcTestStatusLed.description: The CC Test Status LED is a read-only attribute which describes the condition of the CC Test Status light emitting diode located on the CC. This indicates that a service effecting test is in progress and that the LED is illuminated.

hcxCcTestStatusLedChange.name: hcxCcTestStatusLedChange
hcxCcTestStatusLedChange.description: generated whenever there is a change in test LED status. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxCcFaultStatusLed.name: hcxCcFaultStatusLed
hcxCcFaultStatusLed.description: The Ethernet Fault Status LED is a read-only attribute which describes the condition of the ComController Ethernet Fault Status light emitting diode located on the Ethernet board. A value of on(1) indicates that an fault condition has been detected (for which a trap will have been issued) and the LED is illuminated.

hcxCcFaultStatusLedChange.name: hcxCcFaultStatusLedChange
hcxCcFaultStatusLedChange.description: generated whenever there is a change in the Fault LED status. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxCcEtherLinkStatusLed.name: hcxCcEtherLinkStatusLed
hcxCcEtherLinkStatusLed.description: The Ethernet Link Status LED is a read-only attribute which describes the condition of the CC Ethernet Link Status light emitting diode located on the CC board. A value of on(1) indicates that the link is up and active, and that the LED is illuminated. Will be off if no card present.

hcxCcEtherLinkStatusLedChange.name: hcxCcEtherLinkStatusLedChange
hcxCcEtherLinkStatusLedChange.description: generated whenever there is a change in link LED status. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxCcFlashBackupPeriod.name: hcxCcFlashBackupPeriod
hcxCcFlashBackupPeriod.description: The period (in seconds) at which the CC shall automatically backup any configuration data to flash. This must be a multiple of 5 seconds upto 15 minutes. Default is 60 seconds.

hcxCcFlashBackupAction.name: hcxCcFlashBackupAction
hcxCcFlashBackupAction.description: This attribute is used to invoke the Common Controller to save all configuration data to flash.

hcxCcFlashBackupComplete.name: hcxCcFlashBackupComplete
hcxCcFlashBackupComplete.description: This notification is generated whenever the CC card completes a user directed flash backup of configuration. Only severity allowed is WARNING.

hcxCcFlashBackupResult.name: hcxCcFlashBackupResult
hcxCcFlashBackupResult.description: This attribute contains the result of the last CC user directed flash backup.

hcxSwitchSoftwareRevision.name: hcxSwitchSoftwareRevision
hcxSwitchSoftwareRevision.description: software revision of the image loaded on the embedded ATM switch. In the case of the compact ComController this attribute refers to the boot software version.

hcxSwitchHardwareRevision.name: hcxSwitchHardwareRevision
hcxSwitchHardwareRevision.description: hardware revision of the embedded ATM switch. This attribute is only applicable for the compact ComController.

hcxSwitchSerialNumber.name: hcxSwitchSerialNumber
hcxSwitchSerialNumber.description: serial number of the embedded ATM switch. This attribute is only applicable for the compact ComController.

hcxNtpv3Control.name: hcxNtpv3Control
hcxNtpv3Control.description: this attribute controls the NTPv3 feature. This features should NOT be enabled if NMAPS is in use. The timer servers are specified via com21HcxCcNtpGroup. Default diasble.

hcxDiskFaultState.name: hcxDiskFaultState
hcxDiskFaultState.description: this attribute describes the fault state of the PCMCIA disk.

hcxDiskIdentifier.name: hcxDiskIdentifier
hcxDiskIdentifier.description: this attribute indentifies the type of PCMCIA device.

hcxDiskAccessFailure.name: hcxDiskAccessFailure
hcxDiskAccessFailure.description: generated whenever there is a failure to access the PCMCIA disk. Default severity is MAJOR.

hcxDiskAccessFailClear.name: hcxDiskAccessFailClear
hcxDiskAccessFailClear.description: generated whenever a previously reported disk failure is cleared. Severity is CLEARED.

hcxMibVersion.name: hcxMibVersion
hcxMibVersion.description: this attribute specifies the MIB version used by CC.

hcxCcNtpServerIndex.name: hcxCcNtpServerIndex
hcxCcNtpServerIndex.description: this attribute defines both the index of the address entry. The CC shall attempt to access each in order starting with index 1.

hcxCcNtpServerAddress.name: hcxCcNtpServerAddress
hcxCcNtpServerAddress.description: this attribute defines both the IP address of a time server.

hcxCcNtpServerAddrStatus.name: hcxCcNtpServerAddrStatus
hcxCcNtpServerAddrStatus.description: Used to delete or create an entry.
